The paper proposes an approach to tackle challenges in system verification and synthesis by integrating inductive inference, deductive reasoning, and structure hypotheses. This approach is applicable to various domains, including software timing analysis, program synthesis, and controller synthesis for hybrid systems. Therefore, the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, such as Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Software Engineering (cs.SE), Programming Languages (cs.PL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY).
